    <note>Luqiu(1) Xin [24866] He served in personnel administration. My guess is that these Lishui Luqiu are descendants of the Shandong lineage and they moved here at the beginning of the Southern Song. Ming [24867], with the same generational name as Xin, was the first recorded Lishui Luqiu jinshi in 1157. Since Xin held office, he either came from an office-holding family or earned the jinshi, he must have moved to Lishui from elsewhere. I am making Ming, Xin's younger brother, Zhongchen [24868], Xin's son and Zhen [24869], a son of Zhongchen. The exact relationships may be off, but the lineage identification is almost certain. CBD, 5, 3763-4.</note>
